headlines.description: — Dallas coach Jason Kidd had no worries about Luke Doncic's scoring spree disturbing the Mavericks' game plan.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic scores franchise-record 73 points, tied for 4th in NBA history, as Mavs edge Hawks 148-143

headlines.description: — Jalen Green scored 36 points, rookie Cam Whitmore had a career-high 24 points and 11 rebounds and the Houston Rockets routed the Charlotte Hornets 138-104 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Green scores 36 points to help Rockets rout Hornets 138-104

headlines.description: — The Indiana Pacers weathered Devin Booker's early scoring flurry Friday night. Then they stormed back late and stunned the Phoenix Suns.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pacers rally to spoil Devin Booker's 62-point night, stun Suns 133-131

headlines.description: — James Harden had 22 points, 13 assists and 10 rebounds for his 75th career triple-double, Paul George added 21 points and the Los Angeles Clippers thumped the Toronto Raptors 127-107 on Friday night for their fourth consecutive win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harden posts 75th career triple-double as Clippers win 4th straight, beat Raptors 127-107

headlines.description: — Jaren Jackson Jr. had 30 points and eight rebounds, reserve Ziaire Williams added 17 points and the Memphis Grizzlies held on for a 107-106 victory over the Orlando Magic on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jaren Jackson Jr. scores 30, Grizzlies hold on to beat Magic 107-106

headlines.description: — Cleveland Cavaliers coach JB Bickerstaff considered two road matchups with the Milwaukee Bucks in a span of three nights an opportunity to prepare his team for the postseason.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell scores 32 as Cavs beat Bucks 112-100 for 9th win in last 10 games

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 31 points and the Oklahoma City Thunder routed the New Orleans Pelicans 107-83 on Friday night to improve their NBA-leading road record to 15-8.
headlines.shortLinkText: Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scores 31 points to help Thunder rout Pelicans, 107-83

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Jeremy Sochan had 31 points and 14 rebounds, Victor Wembanyama added 23 points and 12 rebounds and the San Antonio Spurs held off Anfernee Simons and the Portland Trail Blazers 116-100 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sochan, Wembanyama help Spurs overcome 40 points from Simons to top Trail Blazers, 116-100
